Description: Landscape with the flight into Egypt; the Holy Family clustered together in the dip of the road beside a tree, with a tall rock in the centre background; after a composition attributed on plate to one of the Carracci Etching
Curator's comments: Similar to some of the plates in the 'Cabinet Jabach', but evidently a later print from the early XVIIIc. The authorship of the drawing is uncertain.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Charles Francis Arnold Howard, 5th Earl of Wicklow
